# API and Context Usage

Optimize every turn so the user’s included usage and rate limits go further. This rule applies to all work in this repo.

## Responses

- Keep answers as short as clarity allows; no filler, repetition, or “engagement” closings.
- Prefer a single well-scoped follow-up over long speculative lists of options.
- Reuse what the user or prior turns already provided instead of re-quoting or re-fetching the same content.

## Tools and file access

- Prefer targeted search (`grep`, codebase search) over opening whole directories or very large files.
- Read only the regions needed (offsets/limits) unless the whole file is required.
- Do not re-read a file in the same task without a reason (e.g. it changed or prior read failed).
- Batch independent reads/searches in parallel when it saves round-trips.
- Skip extra terminal commands, MCP calls, and web fetches unless they are needed to complete the task.

## When stuck

- One precise clarifying question is better than multiple wrong attempts that burn context.

## Scope

- Do not change product behavior, tests, or docs solely to “save tokens.” Optimize *how* the work is done, not *whether* the user’s request is done properly.
